The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 30 minutes more to crack CAT

 New Delhi, July 16 (PTI): The IIMs today announced that the duration of the common entrance test or CAT would be increased by 30 minutes to two-and-a-half hours.

 The institutes also made a special reference to the Centres proposed move to reserve seats for Other Backward Class candidates from 2007-2008.

 The details of the reservation for candidates belonging to OBCs would be notified by the IIMs on their websites and through an advertisement in national newspapers on receipt of an official communication from the appropriate authority, the IIMs said.

 They added that need-based scholarships were available for economically-disadvantaged students.

 It was reported in The Telegraph on July 14 that scoring 50 per cent marks in graduation would be made mandatory for those sitting for CAT from this year. The IIMs announced this today. For SC/ST and disabled candidates, the cut-off is 45 per cent.




